The most problematic of the entire Obama strategy is his plan to withdraw troops from Afghanistan in 18 months and complete this process within three years. The entire Obama doctrine leaves more questions than answers.
Some doubt that the half-increase will have the same effect as the measure in Iraq.
Even despite the fraternal war of recent years, the Iraqi society is relatively well structured, its leaders honoring the values.
The Afghan situation is characterised by contraindication - no one can be trusted and no agreements are held.
Under these conditions, it is difficult to prepare the Afghan security forces, who are accustomed to changing their minds every day.
The political institutions, even if they were formally established correctly, remain only fake buildings behind which patriarchal tribal relations will continue to grow.
The balancing of interests between the different ethnic groups is unusually complicated, especially due to the inconspicuousness of the circumstances that further complicate Pakistan and Iran influences.
The establishment of a “performing state”, which is the minimalist goal of the whole operation, is also very unrealistic.
Time horizon of the Obama strategy astonished by its voluntarism
Over the last eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has only worsened and now it is on the verge of explosion.
Believing that the little soldiers who broke out into the cry of war about the "early homecoming" can do a miracle here, only a truly romantic soul that cannot be impressed by facts.
From a political point of view, the date set for the withdrawal of troops is purely irresponsible, because the Taliban will accept this as the indirect confession of the American defeat.
