Anyone who started the vaccination last year or earlier must also pay for another repeat vaccination themselves.
The first dose of the vaccine must be given between the 3rd and 5th month of life of the child.
Already last year, a quarter of families had their children vaccinated against pneumococcal infections.
The parents paid 1600 crowns and more for a dose.
Vaccination of younger children requires four doses.
Overall, the experts estimate that health insurance companies spend 300,000 to 450,000 crowns a year on vaccine doses.
However, they save on the treatment that children would need without vaccination.
So far, the state has spent about 500,000 per year on all area vaccinations of children.
