Pneumococcal causes middle-ear inflammation, but also severe infections including cerebral skin inflammation and blood poisoning.
As a result of pneumococcal infections, up to 28 children aged up to 10 years die each year after examination in hospitals.
Outside the Czech Republic, the mandatory vaccination of children against pneumococcal infections was introduced in about 40 countries.
Will vaccination be mandatory?
At the same time, it is said that this vaccination could be mandatory in the future.
From January, it will be paid by the insurance companies and voluntary.
