Admiral Nelson’s encounter with an polar bear as a brave 14-year-old flagship to the sea, who only fought with the bullet of his musket, is certainly a legend, but others are true.
Young bears caught swimming behind the bodies of their recently killed mothers were brought to zoos and circuses.
A circus performance at the beginning of the 20th century showed 75 polar bears at a performance.
