A year ago, the hallucinations stopped.
Since she contacted the psychologist Kasten on the internet, she knows exactly that she is not crazy.
Delirium is also a work of art of despair
If someone is socially isolated or suffers from stimulation, they are very likely to have hallucinations after a while, says Kasten.
I suspect the brain is then under-busy and provides for its own entertainment.
Sarah K., a single child, was afraid of other children as a young girl, often playing alone.
